er for 15+ years and fell in love with movement and taking care of myself! I taught fitness classes throughout college and studied Kinesiology (Exercise Science) at The University of Minnesota. It is my passion to help others feel good and love themselves through living a healthy lifestyle. I am a firm believer that living healthy and balanced allows us to better show up for life and our people!&nbsp;</p><p><br></p></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div class="element-wrap" data-label="Text Block" id="e-1606178974728" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606178974728"><div class="elm text-edit"></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" id="e-1606185762176" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606185762176"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b>How did you come to start Fit For Me By Courtney? What’s it like having your own business, and building something you believe in?&nbsp;</b></p><p><b><br></b></p></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" id="e-1606185768311" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606185768311"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>For years, I was doing HIIT workouts (think deep squats and plyo lunges) and I would be hard on myself if I didn’t get a 60 minute workout in 6 days/week. Working out was more of a chore to me and I never truly felt confident in my own skin. In 2018, I transitioned into what is now the Fit For Me method: a mix of Mat Pilates, Barre and Yoga inspired workouts designed to create lean and toned muscles. Since doing FFM workouts, I have never felt better. Inside and out. There is nothing wrong with HIIT or any other style of working out, but it’s all about what works best 